<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 24 at 2:40AM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...PATCHY BLACK ICE POSSIBLE EARLY THIS MORNING...
Spotty very light showers will continue to move across our region
early this morning. This precipitation was very light and
spotty...but road surfaces are still cold. Therefore...these very
light showers may result in patchy black ice even where air
temperatures have risen above freezing. Roads that look damp may
actually be icy...so please drive with caution early this morning.
Temperatures should rise enough by mid-late morning to alleviate
any patchy black ice.</description>
